<%- include("partials/header") -%>
  <div id="sponsership_header" class="wrapper text-center header">
    <h1>SPONSORSHIP</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="info wrapper">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col txt_bx">
        <p>
          The (ISC)² Long Island , New York Chapter is dedicated to the
          advancement of the information security profession, affording our
          members the opportunity to network and educate themselves while
          enriching the surrounding communities.
          <br />
          <br />
          Becoming a sponsor of the (ISC)² Long Island, New York Chapter shows
          that your organization supports the advancement of the information
          security profession. Becoming a sponsor will also create brand
          recognition with our professional members and provide another avenue
          for recruitment of skilled candidates.
          <br />
          <br />
          Sponsorship of the (ISC)² Long Island, New York Chapter entitles
          your organization to the benefits outlined here unless other
          agreements have been made. The sponsorship period runs for one year
          from the time of sign-up. This Sponsorship Plan is referred to in
          the
          <b><a href="" class="text-danger">(ISC)2 Long Island Chapter Sponsorship Agreement.</a></b>
          <br />
          <br />
          If you are interested in becoming a sponsor, please use the form
          below or contact us here.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col pic">
        <h5 class="heading-5">Prospectus</h5>
        <a href=""><img src="/ISC2-LINY-PROSPECTUS.png" alt="" /></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="requirment wrapper">
    <h4 class="heading-4">Requirements</h4>
    <br />
    <p class="para">
      Sponsors of (ISC)² Long Island, New York Chapter must agree to and
      comply with the following conditions. All sponsorships are subject to
      the (ISC)2 Long Island, New York Chapter Board of Directors (BOD)
      approval. This program only applies to the (ISC)² Long Island, New York
      Chapter, and provides no benefits at (ISC)2 or to direct benefits at
      other (ISC)² regional chapters.
    </p>
    <ul class="all">
      <li>
        All sponsorships must comply with the (ISC)2 Long Island, New York
        Chapter mission and should focus on improving the professional
        knowledge of information security practitioners.
      </li>
      <br />
      <li>
        (ISC)2 Long Island, New York Chapter actively enforces a
        non-aggressive marketing policy. (ISC)2 Long Island, New York Chapter
        membership attends (ISC)2 Long Island Chapter, New York events
        regularly for education, information, and professional networking, not
        to be subjected to aggressive marketing tactics.
      </li>
      <br />
      <li>
        “Negative campaigning” against competitors is not permitted. We aim to
        foster a professional atmosphere among members and interested parties
        with the intention of enhancing member recruitment and retention.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

